        {
            "name": "Bloodlash Bush",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "What first appears to be a simple shrub suddenly stirs to life.<br/><br/>The bloodlash bush attempts to lacerate its foes, using its weeping wounds to irrigate the ground around itself. The seeds of a bloodlash bush can take root only in soil that has been soaked in blood.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Plant</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 16",
            "source": {
                "name": "The Fall of Plaguestone",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zoh?Pathfinder-Adventure-The-Fall-of-Plaguestone"
                },
                "page": 62
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Deadly Flora",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Locations",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "These deadly organisms can be found\nin any hot or temperate environment,\nbut like most plants, they need light\nand moisture to thrive.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "The Fall of Plaguestone",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zoh?Pathfinder-Adventure-The-Fall-of-Plaguestone"
                        },
                        "page": 62
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Treasure",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "While most forms of deadly flora\ndo not value treasure in any way,\ntheir victims\u2019 wealth can usually be\nfound strewn about their location,\nsometimes even buried in their\nroots. Due to the outdoors, the only\nthings of value that are typically\nfound are made from metal or\nstone, like weapons, armor, and\nsome talismans.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "The Fall of Plaguestone",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zoh?Pathfinder-Adventure-The-Fall-of-Plaguestone"
                        },
                        "page": 62
                    },
                    "subtype": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Often overlooked in light of more obvious threats, some plants can be just as deadly and dangerous as wild beasts.",
